    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.2: The extracellular domains of neuronal pentraxin receptor (NPR-ECD) and the secreted neuronal pentraxins NP1 and NARP (NP2) directly bind to GluA1-NTD\nFig.3: NPR, NP1, and NARP binding enhances GluA1 function.\n\n1/11/2017 Pim\n- The action of NP2 is not shown in synaptic setting but in HEK cells. The function of NP2 is inferred to also take place on synaptic AMPARs.. Experimental description: Mouse hippocampal neurons were prepared.\n\n23/6/2017 Pim\n-All overexpression constructs are of human species: \"The constructs encoding cDNAs of hNPR (HsCD00083063), hNP1 (HsCD00296108), and hNARP (HsCD00040444) were obtained from PlasmID (http://plasmid.med.harvard.edu/PLASMID/).\"\n- Species of GluA1-NTD overexpressed protein is not mentioned.",
